transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yes. How are you?

Speaker 1: How are we doing? Good, thank you for asking.

Speaker 2: Good. I need to cancel getting any more of the Scor-Blue, at least until further notice.

Speaker 1: I got so much now, I can't use this in three years.

Speaker 2: Oh, sure. Mr. Gregory Crane?

Speaker 1: That's correct.

Speaker 2: I see that you have a prescription from Dr. Supa for Viagra, 50 mg, 10 tablets, every 30 days.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So I can tell the pharmacy to stop the 30 days and pause the prescription.

Speaker 1: I think they pause it to lock your pricing, I think, up to half a year,

Speaker 2: so you don't get it on a monthly anymore, but you can get it once or twice a year.

Speaker 1: No, just let me do this. Let me call you when I run out.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I got the number. Just cancel. Don't send me any more. I don't need any. I got plenty.

Speaker 2: No, I got you. I got you. You don't need to send yourself if you don't need it, obviously.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So what I was saying, for you to reorder, you got to have the doctor prescription,

Speaker 1: because if you lose that, when you reorder, price will be different.

Speaker 2: They got to reinvest. So what I was trying to do is advise the pharmacy to pause up to half a year,

Speaker 1: so there is no more monthly moving forward.

Speaker 2: Even after a year, don't send me any.

Speaker 1: Okay, I see.

Speaker 2: We're going to have to just cancel everything then.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Because what they do, they require to get just a refill once or twice a year.

Speaker 1: But if you don't need it, that's fine. I'm just going to cancel everything.

Speaker 2: Yes. I've done this before. I've had to cancel before because I got so much.

Speaker 1: I keep getting so much, I can't use it. So just cancel it.

Speaker 2: If it's twice as much next time, it'll just be twice as much. I'll understand.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: You got it.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. Yes, sir. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Okay, bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
